WITH experiment_data AS (
	SELECT 
    	CASE WHEN ARRAYS_OVERLAP(ndxgrp, 
            ARRAY['#b15:idxmatchingcontrolplane_e275','#B15:idxmatchingcontrolplane_e275']) 
            THEN 'test' ELSE 'control' END AS _group, 
        q, jobid
    FROM organic -- TABLESAMPLE BERNOULLI (10) -- sampling rate
    WHERE 
    	unixtime >= imhotep_unixtime('2024-10-15') AND unixtime < imhotep_unixtime('2024-11-12') -- test start date & end date
        AND country = 'ca'
        AND ARRAYS_OVERLAP(ndxgrp, 
        	ARRAY['#b15:idxmatchingcontrolplane_e274','#B15:idxmatchingcontrolplane_e274',
            	  '#b15:idxmatchingcontrolplane_e275','#B15:idxmatchingcontrolplane_e275'])
)

SELECT 
	_group, 
    COUNT_IF(answer='No') as bad_matches, 
    COUNT() AS all_labels, 
    COUNT_IF(answer='No') / CAST(COUNT() AS DOUBLE) AS BMR
FROM jobtoqueryrelevance
INNER JOIN experiment_data ON
	jobtoqueryrelevance.query = experiment_data.q
    AND jobtoqueryrelevance.jobid = experiment_data.jobid
WHERE 
	jobtoqueryrelevance.unixtime >= imhotep_unixtime('2024-01-01') AND jobtoqueryrelevance.unixtime < imhotep_unixtime('2024-11-12')
	AND jobtoqueryrelevance.country='CA'
GROUP BY _group

with jobs as (SELECT coalesce(parent_company_id, job_source_id+1000000) as parent_company_id 
, coalesce(max(parent_company_name), max(job_source_name)) as parent_company_name   
, min(job_source_id) as job_source_id
, count(distinct agg_job_id) as jobs_l30days 
, sum(organic_apply_starts) as orgAS_l30days 

FROM datalake.imhotep.jobactivitymetrics j
WHERE unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('30d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today')
and job_country_code = 'US' and is_job_searchable > 0 
--and parent_company_id is not null 
and advertiser_type not in ('Test', 'Indeed')
group by 1)

, rev as (select parent_company_id 
, sum(net_revenue_cents)/100 as spend_lyear 
FROM datalake.imhotep.grdm j 
WHERE unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('1y') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today') 
group by 1) 

, together as (select jobs.* 
, coalesce(spend_lyear, 0) as spend_lyear 
, coalesce(last_any_products, cast('2000-01-01' as date)) as last_revenue_date  -- if no last revenue date, then say they last spend in 2000 
, date_diff('day', coalesce(last_any_products, cast('2000-01-01' as date)), CURRENT_DATE) as days_since_last_spend 
from jobs 
left join rev on rev.parent_company_id = jobs.parent_company_id 
left join datalake.core.product_analytics_fct_first_last_activity_dates_parent f 
	on f.parent_company_id = jobs.parent_company_id
--where jobs_l30days > 100    
)
, together_ordered as (select *, 
ntile(10) over (order by jobs_l30days desc) as jobs_ntile -- 1 is most jobs 
, ntile(10) over (order by spend_lyear asc) as spend_ntile -- 1 is lowest spend 
, ntile(10) over (order by days_since_last_spend desc) as days_since_last_spend_ntile -- 1 is never spender
from together )

, together_ordered_fixed as (select parent_company_id  
, job_source_id
, parent_company_name 
, orgAS_l30days 
, jobs_l30days
, days_since_last_spend
, spend_lyear
, jobs_ntile 
, case when spend_lyear <= 0 then 1 else spend_ntile end as spend_ntile 
, case when days_since_last_spend > 9000 then 1 else days_since_last_spend_ntile end as days_since_last_spend_ntile

from together_ordered )

, rfm as (select * 
, jobs_ntile + spend_ntile + days_since_last_spend_ntile as rfm_unweighted 
, 1*jobs_ntile + 100*spend_ntile + 10*days_since_last_spend_ntile as rfm_weighted -- the higher this number the bigger the penalty
from together_ordered_fixed
order by 1*jobs_ntile + 100*spend_ntile + 10*days_since_last_spend_ntile desc
)

, jobs_first_hour as (SELECT sourceid
, jobid  
, max(normtitle) as normtitle 
, coalesce(max(jlmsa), 'rural') as msa 
, sum(coalesce(applystarts,0)) as applystarts

FROM datalake.imhotep.searchimpressions j
WHERE unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('30d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today')
and country in ('us', 'US') and sponsored = 0 and jobageminutes <= 60
group by 1, 2)

, jobs_first_hour_ordered as (SELECT * 
, ntile(10) over (order by applystarts asc) as job_ntile
FROM jobs_first_hour)


, subset as (select case when rfm_weighted > 1000 then 'A_1000+ Biggest Penalty'
when rfm_weighted > 900 then 'B_900'
when rfm_weighted > 800 then 'C_800'
when rfm_weighted > 700 then 'D_700'
when rfm_weighted > 600 then 'E_600'
when rfm_weighted > 500 then 'F_500'
when rfm_weighted > 400 then 'G_400'
when rfm_weighted > 300 then 'H_300'
when rfm_weighted > 200 then 'I_200' else 'J_100 Lowest Penalty' end as rfm_segment 
, rfm.* 
, j.* 
, row_number() over (partition by job_source_id order by applystarts desc) as rn 

from rfm  
left join jobs_first_hour_ordered j on j.sourceid = rfm.job_source_id 
where rfm_weighted > 1000 or rfm_weighted < 200
and j.job_ntile = 10 )

select * from subset where rn <= 5

WHERE ce.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('181d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('1d')
and   cc.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('195d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('1d')

, agg as (

select advertiserId
      ,count(*) as totalMessages
      ,count_if(isEmail) as emailMessages
      ,count_if(NOT isEmail) as onPlatformMessages 
  from convos
group by 1 

		)
        
,advertiserDetails as ( 

select advertiser_id
   , max_by(parent_company_size_segment, unixtime) as parent_company_size_segment
   , max_by(type, unixtime) as type
   , max_by(billing_country, unixtime) as billing_country
  from  daily_employer2 
  where unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2d') and IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('1d')
group by 1

   )
        

 select 
            case when emailMessages> 0 and onPlatformMessages=0 then 'Email Only'
			 when  emailMessages=0 and onPlatformMessages>0 then 'Chat Only'
			 when  emailMessages>0 and onPlatformMessages>0 then 'Email & Chat'
             end as usageType
        ,count(distinct advertiserId) as empCountDistinct
        ,100.0*count(distinct advertiserId)/sum(count(distinct advertiserId)) over() as empCountDistinct
        ,count() as empCount
        ,100.0*count()/sum(count()) over() as pctEmpCount

  from agg
left join advertiserDetails on agg.advertiserId=advertiserDetails.advertiser_id
where parent_company_size_segment='S'
group by 1
order by 1

    FROM javaruntimeversions
    WHERE unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('4y') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today')
    GROUP BY appid, env, runId, unixtime
), most_recent_runs AS (

    FROM most_recent_starts mrs
    LEFT JOIN javaruntimeversions jrv ON mrs.runId=jrv.runId AND mrs.startup_num=1
    WHERE jrv.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('4y') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today')

WITH daily_data AS (
    SELECT
        date_trunc('minute', from_unixtime(lp.unixtime)) as date,
        moderationApi, 
        moderationType, 
		SUM(SUM(CAST(lp.flagged  AS DOUBLE))) OVER (partition by moderationApi, moderationType ORDER BY date_trunc('minute', from_unixtime(lp.unixtime)) ROWS BETWEEN 30 PRECEDING AND current row) AS block_count,
		SUM(COUNT(*)) OVER (partition by moderationApi, moderationType ORDER BY date_trunc('minute', from_unixtime(lp.unixtime)) ROWS BETWEEN 30 PRECEDING AND current row) AS request_count,
		SUM(SUM(CAST(lp.flagged  AS DOUBLE))) OVER (partition by moderationApi, moderationType ORDER BY date_trunc('minute', from_unixtime(lp.unixtime)) ROWS BETWEEN 240 + 30 PRECEDING AND 30 PRECEDING) AS weekly_block_count,
		SUM(COUNT(*)) OVER (partition by moderationApi, moderationType ORDER BY date_trunc('minute', from_unixtime(lp.unixtime)) ROWS BETWEEN 240 + 30 PRECEDING AND 30 PRECEDING) AS weekly_request_count
    FROM
      	datalake.imhotep.llmproxy lp -- switching to imhotep for speed even though there is a 1D data lag
        --logrepo.log.llm_proxy lp
    WHERE
        lp.flagged IS NOT NULL
        AND lp.metric = 'moderation-text'
        AND unixtime BETWEEN imhotep_unixtime(timestamp '2024-10-24') AND imhotep_unixtime(timestamp '2024-10-29')
        and appName='ContentGenerationService' and moderationApi='openAIModerations' and moderationType='input'
    GROUP BY
        date_trunc('minute', from_unixtime(lp.unixtime)),
        moderationApi, 
        moderationType 
),
block_rate AS (
    SELECT
        date,
        moderationApi, 
        moderationType,
        request_count,
        weekly_request_count,
        cast(request_count * 240 as double) / cast(30 * weekly_request_count as double) as relative_request_rate,
        cast(block_count as double) / request_count as raw_block_rate,
        -- We adjust the proportion estimates by adding z^2/2 successes and z^2/2 failures (z^2 obs total) to the counts.
        -- This can be thought of as a Bayesian prior, or as a correction to the Normal approximation for rates close to 0 or 1.
        -- For large values of request_count this converges to the raw proportion (block_rate ~ raw_block_rate).
        -- Using z=3.0, in other words, we're going to require a "3-sigma" detection.
        cast(block_count + 4.5 as double) / (request_count + 9.0) as block_rate, -- corrected/smoothed
        cast(block_count as double) / (request_count + 9.0) as block_rate_zc, -- zero-centered corrected/smoothed rate (only adding to denominator)
        cast(weekly_block_count + (240 * 4.5 / 30) as double) / (weekly_request_count + (240 * 9.0 / 30)) as  weekly_block_rate, -- corrected/smoothed
        cast(weekly_block_count as double) / (weekly_request_count + (240 * 9.0 / 30)) as  weekly_block_rate_zc, -- corrected/smoothed        
        cast(weekly_block_count as double) /  weekly_request_count as raw_weekly_block_rate,  
        (cast(block_count + 4.5 as double) / (request_count + 9.0)) - (cast(weekly_block_count + (240 * 4.5 / 30) as double) / (weekly_request_count + (240 * 9.0 / 30))) as change,
        sum(1.0) over (partition by moderationApi, moderationType ORDER BY date ROWS BETWEEN 240 + 30 PRECEDING AND 1 PRECEDING) as previous_dates_count
    FROM
        daily_data
),

block_rate_change AS (
    SELECT
        date,
        moderationApi, 
        moderationType,
        request_count,
		relative_request_rate,        
        weekly_request_count,
        STDDEV(block_rate-weekly_block_rate) OVER (partition by moderationApi, moderationType ORDER BY date ROWS BETWEEN 240 + 30 PRECEDING AND 30 PRECEDING) AS stddev_obs,
        SQRT((block_rate * (1.0 - block_rate) / request_count) + ((weekly_block_rate * (1.0 - weekly_block_rate) / weekly_request_count))) as stddev_approx,
        raw_block_rate,  
        block_rate,
        block_rate_zc,
        weekly_block_rate_zc,
        raw_weekly_block_rate,  
        weekly_block_rate, -- corrected/smoothed
        change,
        case weekly_block_rate_zc
           when 0 then 0
           else (block_rate_zc - weekly_block_rate_zc) 
        end as change_zc,
		previous_dates_count             
    FROM
        block_rate
),
confidence_interval AS (
    SELECT
        date,
        moderationApi, 
        moderationType,
        stddev_obs,
		stddev_approx,
        greatest(stddev_approx, stddev_obs) as stddev,
        block_rate,
        block_rate - 6 * greatest(stddev_approx, stddev_obs)  AS block_rate_lower_bound,
        block_rate + 6 * greatest(stddev_approx, stddev_obs) AS block_rate_upper_bound,          
        weekly_block_rate,
		weekly_request_count,
		raw_block_rate,        
        raw_weekly_block_rate,        
        change,
        change_zc,
        block_rate_zc,
        weekly_block_rate_zc,
        request_count,
		relative_request_rate,                
        change - 6 * greatest(stddev_approx, stddev_obs) AS change_lower_bound,
        change + 6 * greatest(stddev_approx, stddev_obs) AS change_upper_bound,
        previous_dates_count,
        row_number() OVER (partition by moderationApi, moderationType ORDER BY date) as row_n         
    FROM
        block_rate_change
    --WHERE
    --	weekly_request_count > 100
    --    and request_count > 100
)
SELECT
    date,
    moderationApi, 
    moderationType,
    request_count,
	relative_request_rate,            
    stddev_obs,
    stddev_approx,
    stddev,
    block_rate,
	block_rate_lower_bound,
    block_rate_upper_bound,
    weekly_block_rate,
    weekly_request_count,
        raw_block_rate,        
        raw_weekly_block_rate,    
change,
    change / weekly_block_rate as relative_change,
    change_zc / weekly_block_rate_zc as relative_change_zc,
    change_zc,
    block_rate_zc,
    weekly_block_rate_zc,        
    change_lower_bound,
    change_upper_bound,
    change_lower_bound * 1.0 / weekly_block_rate as relative_change_lower_bound,
    change_upper_bound * 1.0 / weekly_block_rate as relative_change_upper_bound,
    greatest(change_lower_bound / weekly_block_rate, 0) as relative_change_lower_bound_sig,
    least(change_upper_bound / weekly_block_rate, 0) as relative_change_upper_bound_sig,     
    IF((change_lower_bound > 0 or change_upper_bound<0) and (previous_dates_count > 240), 1, 0) as is_sig_change,
    IF((change_lower_bound > 0 or change_upper_bound<0) and (date = (max(date) over ())) and (previous_dates_count > 6), 1, 0) as is_latest_date_sig_change,
    change/stddev as z_score,
    IF(date = (max(date) over ()), change/stddev, NULL) as latest_date_z_score, 
    max(date) over () as latest_data_date,
    previous_dates_count            
FROM
    confidence_interval -- Note: return values for all dates unlike with the alerting query
WHERE
    (change/stddev) IS NOT NULL
    and ((row_n % 15 = 0)  or (abs(change/stddev) > 6))
    and previous_dates_count > (0.9 * 240)
ORDER BY
    date DESC, moderationApi ASC, moderationType DESC

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT accountid) AS distinct_account_count
FROM datalake.imhotep.passsigninattempt
WHERE unixtime > IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('1month') AND successful = 1

-- Trigger RB Rules:

-- Rules w/ Payments cat
WITH rules AS (
    SELECT rule_id, created_by, rule_state, responses
    FROM rulebook_snapshot rs
    WHERE unixtime BETWEEN imhotep_unixtime('1d') AND imhotep_unixtime('today')
    AND context = 'advertiser'
    AND (
        REGEXP_LIKE(LOWER(rule), 'triggeredrulenames') 
        OR REGEXP_LIKE(LOWER(rule), 'triggeredruleids')
        OR rule_id IN (4800, 4803, 4605, 4853, 4864, 4854, 3161, 3160, 2615, 
                       3257, 3282, 3341, 3346, 3350, 2597, 2610, 4505, 3362, 
                       3267, 4080, 3363, 2616, 3499, 4174, 4183, 4703)
    	)
    AND rule_state = 'ACTIVE'
    GROUP BY 1,2,3,4
),

-- Advertisers that matched rules from the CTE above
rule_matches AS (
    SELECT ruleid, contentkey
    FROM rulecontentresult rc
    INNER JOIN rules r ON r.rule_id = rc.ruleid
    WHERE unixtime BETWEEN imhotep_unixtime('2024-01-01') AND imhotep_unixtime('7d') --change rule match date here
    AND match = 1
    GROUP BY 1,2
),

-- Advertisers info that matched payments rules
dmod AS (
    SELECT ruleid, advertiserid, showhostedjobs, industry
    FROM dradismod dmod
    INNER JOIN rule_matches rm ON CAST(dmod.advertiserid AS VARCHAR) = rm.contentkey
    WHERE unixtime BETWEEN imhotep_unixtime('2d') AND imhotep_unixtime('1d')
    AND showhostedjobs != 'pending'
    AND industry != 'Job Seeker'
    GROUP BY 1,2,3,4
),

rule_metrics AS (
    SELECT 
        ruleid,
        COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN industry = 'Fraud/Scam' THEN advertiserid END) AS fraud_count,
        COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN showhostedjobs = 'rejected' THEN advertiserid END) AS rejected_count,
        COUNT(DISTINCT advertiserid) AS all_count, 
        ROUND(COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN industry = 'Fraud/Scam' THEN advertiserid END) / CAST(COUNT(DISTINCT advertiserid) AS DOUBLE) * 100,2) AS fraud_perc,
        ROUND(COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN showhostedjobs = 'rejected' THEN advertiserid END) / CAST(COUNT(DISTINCT advertiserid) AS DOUBLE) * 100,2) AS rejection_perc
    FROM dmod
    GROUP BY 1
)

-- Left join on the first CTE with the rule_metrics CTE to get an output with all rule values (null values coalesced to zero)
SELECT
    rule_id, 
    created_by, 
    rule_state, 
    COALESCE(fraud_count,0) AS fraud_count,
    COALESCE(rejected_count,0) AS rejected_count,
    COALESCE(all_count,0) AS all_count,
    COALESCE(fraud_perc,0) AS fraud_perc,
    COALESCE(rejection_perc,0) AS rejection_perc
FROM rules r
LEFT JOIN rule_metrics rm ON rm.ruleid = r.rule_id
GROUP BY 1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8
ORDER BY all_count DESC

WITH opened_daemonizer_mrs AS (
    SELECT path_with_namespace_plus_mr_iid
    FROM imhotep.gitlabevents ge 
    WHERE 
        ge.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2024-04-01') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today')
        AND action='open'
        AND gitlabhook_objectattributes_title LIKE '%Daemonizer Migration%'
), flow AS (
    SELECT 
    	path_with_namespace_plus_mr_iid AS merge_request_id, 
        action, 
        CASE 
        	WHEN action = 'open' THEN FROM_UNIXTIME(CAST(gitlabhook_objectattributes_createdat AS DOUBLE))
            ELSE FROM_UNIXTIME(gitlabhook_objectattributes_updatedat) 
        END AS action_time,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY path_with_namespace_plus_mr_iid, action ORDER BY gitlabhook_objectattributes_updatedat ASC) AS step_number
    FROM imhotep.gitlabevents ge 
    WHERE 
        ge.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2024-04-01') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today')
        AND ge.path_with_namespace_plus_mr_iid IN (SELECT path_with_namespace_plus_mr_iid FROM opened_daemonizer_mrs)
        AND action NOT IN ('null')
    ORDER BY path_with_namespace_plus_mr_iid, gitlabhook_objectattributes_updatedat ASC
), steps AS (
	SELECT merge_request_id, action, action_time
	FROM flow 
	WHERE step_number = 1  -- don't show repeated chains of MR updates
	ORDER BY merge_request_id, action_time ASC
), agg_steps AS (
	SELECT 
    	merge_request_id, 
        ARRAY_JOIN(ARRAY_AGG(action ORDER BY action_time, action), ',') AS steps 
    FROM steps 
    GROUP BY merge_request_id
)

--SELECT * FROM steps ORDER BY merge_request_id, action_time

SELECT steps, COUNT(merge_request_id) AS num_values FROM agg_steps GROUP BY steps

	COUNT(*) as total_profile_views, 
   	SUM(r.sent) as outreaches,
    SUM(r.resp_pos) as resp_pos,
    COUNT(js.account_id) as profile_with_linkedIn,
    ROUND(CAST(SUM(r.sent) AS DOUBLE) * 100 / COUNT(*), 1) as outreach_rate
FROM 
	datalake.imhotep.rsresumeview v

LEFT JOIN
	datalake.imhotep.rscontacts r
ON
	v.recruiterAccountId = r.senderAccountId
    AND v.resumeAccountId = r.recipientAccountId
    AND r.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('29d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('1d')

LEFT JOIN 
	datalake.imhotep.js_fact_store_snapshot_prod js

	v.resumeAccountId = js.account_id

    AND js.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('29d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('1d')

WHERE 
	v.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('29d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('1d')
    AND js.account_id IS NOT NULL -- with LinkedIn link

WITH 

subscription_attributes AS (

	SELECT subscription_id, DATE(purchased_at) AS last_purchase_date
    FROM datalake.core.product_analytics_dim_resume_subscription_current
    
    	
),

rsContacts AS (

    SELECT	
    	DATE(FROM_UNIXTIME(unixtime)) AS activity_date,
        subscriptionid AS subscription_id,
        advertiserid AS advertiser_id,
        IF(source = 'MATCHES', 'Match', 'Search') AS product,
        IF(subscriptiontier = 'PROFESSIONAL' 
        	AND (last_purchase_date < DATE('2024-04-02') OR last_purchase_date IS NULL)
            AND source != 'MATCHES', 'Legacy Search', 'Smart Sourcing') AS subscription_tier,
        SUM(sent) AS contacts_sent,
        SUM(resp_any) AS all_responses,
        SUM(resp_pos) AS positive_responses
    FROM 
    	datalake.imhotep.rsContacts rsContacts
    LEFT JOIN
        subscription_attributes 
        	ON rsContacts.subscriptionid = subscription_attributes.subscription_id
    WHERE 
    	unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2024-04-02') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today') 
	GROUP BY 1, 2, 3, 4, 5

)

SELECT
	subscription_tier,
    COUNT(DISTINCT advertiser_id) AS num_advertisers,
    COUNT(DISTINCT subscription_id) AS num_subscriptions,
    SUM(contacts_sent) AS contacts_sent,
    SUM(all_responses) AS all_responses,
    (SUM(all_responses) * 1.0000) / SUM(contacts_sent) AS all_response_rate,
    SUM(positive_responses) AS positive_responses,
    (SUM(positive_responses) * 1.0000) / SUM(contacts_sent) AS positive_response_rate
FROM 
	rsContacts
WHERE advertiser_id = 2489298

GROUP BY 1

-- What are the largest clusters which exactly match between legacy and mvp?
-- Do the bin files in the jobindex artifact exactly match for those jobs?

with
--lets try to collect the clusters into sets, a special case for adding the original into the set also
cluster_job_array_prep as
(   select modelId,
           concat(radArtifactName, '-', modelId, '-', runStartTime) as model,
           originalJobId as originalRepostId,
           array_distinct(array_agg(jobCopyJobId)) as copyJobIds
    from datalake.imhotep.duplicationDetectionRadContents
    where imhotep_unixtime('1d') <= unixtime and unixtime < imhotep_unixtime('1d') + 24*60*60
    and modelId in ('Legacy RepostDetector', 'legacyRepostModel-2.2')
    and   imhotep_unixtime('1000d') <= jobCopyCreateDate/1000 and jobCopyCreateDate/1000 < imhotep_unixtime('0d')
    group by 1,2,3
),
legacy_cluster_job_arrays as
(   select model,
           originalRepostId,
           array_min(array_union(copyJobIds, array [originalRepostId])) as newRepostId,
           array_sort(array_distinct(array_union(copyJobIds, array [originalRepostId]))) as jobIds
    from cluster_job_array_prep
    where modelId='Legacy RepostDetector'
),
mvp_cluster_job_arrays as
(   select model,
           originalRepostId,
           array_min(array_union(copyJobIds, array [originalRepostId])) as newRepostId,
           array_sort(array_distinct(array_union(copyJobIds, array [originalRepostId]))) as jobIds
    from cluster_job_array_prep
    where modelId='legacyRepostModel-2.2'
)

        WHEN DATE_TRUNC('week', ppp_last_active) < DATE_TRUNC('week', ppc_last_active) THEN 'PPC Migration started - only active on PPC'
        WHEN DATE_TRUNC('week', ppp_last_active) >= DATE_TRUNC('week', ppc_last_active) THEN 'PPC Migration started - still active on PPP'
        WHEN ppp_last_active IS NULL THEN 'PPC - Acquired on PPC no prior PPP'
	END AS migration_status,

            company_id,

		FROM 
        	datalake.imhotep.recruit_company_jobs
		WHERE

		GROUP BY

	),

	(
        SELECT 
            r.company_id, 
            DATE_TRUNC('week', FROM_UNIXTIME(unixtime)) AS week,
            ppc_migration_date,

            COUNT(DISTINCT DATE_TRUNC('day', FROM_UNIXTIME(unixtime))) AS active_days
        FROM 
            datalake.imhotep.recruit_company_jobs r
        INNER JOIN
            migration_date m
            ON r.company_id = m.company_id
        WHERE
            unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2022-01-01') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today')
            --Only include migrated companies
            AND ppc_migration_date IS NOT NULL
            AND ppp_last_date IS NOT NULL
        GROUP BY 
            1, 2, 3
        HAVING
            SUM(rev) > 0
    ),
pre_post_active_days AS
	(
    	SELECT
    		company_id,
            SUM(CASE WHEN week < ppc_migration_date THEN active_days END) AS pre_migration_active_days,
            SUM(CASE WHEN week >= ppc_migration_date THEN active_days END) AS post_migration_active_days
		FROM weekly_rev
        GROUP BY
        	1

pre_migration_weekly_baseline AS

    ),

        	ON r.company_id = b.company_id

            SUM(CASE WHEN product = 'indeedplus' THEN 1 END) AS ppc_count,
            --Identify PPP activity after PPC migration has already started within the same month
            SUM(CASE WHEN

                AND FROM_UNIXTIME(unixtime) > ppc_migration_date 
			THEN 1 END) AS ppp_after_ppc_count

                    AND month > migration_month)
					OR ((COALESCE(ppp_after_ppc_count, 0)) > 0 AND month = migration_month)
				THEN 'PPC Migration started - still active on PPP'

		SUM(SUM(CAST(lp.flagged  AS DOUBLE))) OVER (partition by moderationApi, moderationType ORDER BY date_trunc('minute', from_unixtime(lp.unixtime)) ROWS BETWEEN 240 + 30 PRECEDING AND 30 PRECEDING) AS weekly_block_count,
		SUM(COUNT(*)) OVER (partition by moderationApi, moderationType ORDER BY date_trunc('minute', from_unixtime(lp.unixtime)) ROWS BETWEEN 240 + 30 PRECEDING AND 30 PRECEDING) AS weekly_request_count
    FROM

    WHERE

block_rate AS (
    SELECT
        date,
        moderationApi, 
        moderationType,
        request_count,
        weekly_request_count,
        cast(request_count * 240 as double) / cast(30 * weekly_request_count as double) as relative_request_rate,
        cast(block_count as double) / request_count as raw_block_rate,
        -- We adjust the proportion estimates by adding z^2/2 successes and z^2/2 failures (z^2 obs total) to the counts.
        -- This can be thought of as a Bayesian prior, or as a correction to the Normal approximation for rates close to 0 or 1.
        -- For large values of request_count this converges to the raw proportion (block_rate ~ raw_block_rate).
        -- Using z=3.0, in other words, we're going to require a "3-sigma" detection.
        cast(block_count + 4.5 as double) / (request_count + 9.0) as block_rate, -- corrected/smoothed
        cast(block_count as double) / (request_count + 9.0) as block_rate_zc, -- zero-centered corrected/smoothed rate (only adding to denominator)
        cast(weekly_block_count + (240 * 4.5 / 30) as double) / (weekly_request_count + (240 * 9.0 / 30)) as  weekly_block_rate, -- corrected/smoothed
        cast(weekly_block_count as double) / (weekly_request_count + (240 * 9.0 / 30)) as  weekly_block_rate_zc, -- corrected/smoothed        
        cast(weekly_block_count as double) /  weekly_request_count as raw_weekly_block_rate,  
        (cast(block_count + 4.5 as double) / (request_count + 9.0)) - (cast(weekly_block_count + (240 * 4.5 / 30) as double) / (weekly_request_count + (240 * 9.0 / 30))) as change,

        SQRT((block_rate * (1.0 - block_rate) / request_count) + ((weekly_block_rate * (1.0 - weekly_block_rate) / weekly_request_count))) as stddev_approx,
        raw_block_rate,  
        block_rate,

        block_rate + 6 * greatest(stddev_approx, stddev_obs) AS block_rate_upper_bound,

		weekly_request_count,
		raw_block_rate,

        change - 6 * greatest(stddev_approx, stddev_obs) AS change_lower_bound,

        previous_dates_count,
        row_number() OVER (partition by moderationApi, moderationType ORDER BY date) as row_n

change,

WITH migration_date AS
	(
		SELECT  
            company_id, 
			MIN(CASE WHEN COALESCE(product, '') = 'indeedplus' THEN FROM_UNIXTIME(unixtime) END) AS ppc_migration_date,
			MAX(CASE WHEN COALESCE(product, '') <> 'indeedplus' THEN FROM_UNIXTIME(unixtime) END) AS ppp_last_date,
            --Last activity date regardless of whether PPC or PPP
            MAX(FROM_UNIXTIME(unixtime)) AS all_last_date
		FROM 
        	datalake.imhotep.recruit_company_jobs
		WHERE 
        	unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2022-01-01') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today')
		GROUP BY
        	1
	),
monthly_companies AS
	(
		SELECT  
        	c.company_id, 
			CAST(DATE_TRUNC('month', FROM_UNIXTIME(unixtime)) AS DATE) AS month
		FROM 
        	datalake.imhotep.recruit_company_jobs c
		WHERE 
        	unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2023-04-01') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today')
		GROUP BY 
        	1, 2
	),
monthly_companies_labelled AS
	(
		SELECT
			c.company_id,
            month,
            CASE
            	WHEN month = CAST(DATE_TRUNC('month', all_last_date) AS DATE) THEN 1 
			END AS final_active_month_flag,
            CASE 
            	WHEN 
                    ppc_migration_date IS NULL 
                    --Retain yet to migrate label for months prior to migration starting
                    OR month < CAST(DATE_TRUNC('month', ppc_migration_date) AS DATE) 
                THEN 'Yet to start PPC migration'
				WHEN
                	--Assign migration started label from first month with PPC activity onwards
                	CAST(DATE_TRUNC('month', ppc_migration_date) AS DATE) <= month 
				THEN 'PPC Migration started'
			END AS cohort
		FROM 
        	monthly_companies c
        LEFT JOIN
        	migration_date m
            ON c.company_id = m.company_id 
	)
SELECT
	month, 
    cohort, 
    COUNT(DISTINCT company_id) AS companies, 
    SUM(final_active_month_flag) AS fully_churned_companies,
	100*(1e0*SUM(final_active_month_flag)/COUNT(DISTINCT company_id)) AS fully_churned_rate
FROM 
	monthly_companies_labelled
WHERE 
	month < DATE_TRUNC('month', CURRENT_DATE)
GROUP BY 
	1, 2
ORDER BY
	1

    SELECT
        IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2month') AS start_date,
        IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today') AS end_date
)

    FROM datalake.core.product_analytics_dim_resume_subscription_current
    
    	
),

rsContacts AS (

    SELECT	
    	DATE(FROM_UNIXTIME(unixtime)) AS activity_date,
        subscriptionid AS subscription_id,
        advertiserid AS advertiser_id,
        IF(source = 'MATCHES', 'Match', 'Search') AS product,
        IF(subscriptiontier = 'PROFESSIONAL' 
        	AND (last_purchase_date < DATE('2024-08-02') OR last_purchase_date IS NULL)
            AND source != 'MATCHES', 'Legacy Search', 'Smart Sourcing') AS subscription_tier,
        SUM(sent) AS contacts_sent,
        SUM(resp_any) AS all_responses,
        SUM(resp_pos) AS positive_responses
    FROM 
    	datalake.imhotep.rsContacts rsContacts
    LEFT JOIN
        subscription_attributes 
        	ON rsContacts.subscriptionid = subscription_attributes.subscription_id
    WHERE 
    	unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2024-08-02') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today') 
	GROUP BY 1, 2, 3, 4, 5

)

SELECT
	subscription_tier,
    COUNT(DISTINCT advertiser_id) AS num_advertisers,
    COUNT(DISTINCT subscription_id) AS num_subscriptions,
    SUM(contacts_sent) AS contacts_sent,
    SUM(all_responses) AS all_responses,
    (SUM(all_responses) * 1.0000) / SUM(contacts_sent) AS all_response_rate,
    SUM(positive_responses) AS positive_responses,
    (SUM(positive_responses) * 1.0000) / SUM(contacts_sent) AS positive_response_rate
FROM 
	rsContacts
WHERE advertiser_id = 16775855

GROUP BY 1

WITH test_adids AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT adid
    FROM datalake.imhotep.adCampaignPerformanceTest51
    WHERE unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2024-09-26 00:00:00') 
                      AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2024-09-26 08:00:00')
),
verification_adids AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT adid
    FROM datalake.imhotep.adCampaignPerformanceVerification
    WHERE unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2024-09-26 00:00:00') 
                      AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2024-09-26 08:00:00')
),
adids_in_test_not_in_verification AS (
    SELECT adid
    FROM test_adids
    EXCEPT
    SELECT adid
    FROM verification_adids
),
adids_in_verification_not_in_test AS (
    SELECT adid
    FROM verification_adids
    EXCEPT
    SELECT adid
    FROM test_adids
)
SELECT
    'adids_in_test_not_in_verification' AS difference_type,
    ARRAY_AGG(adid) AS adid_list
FROM (
    SELECT adid
    FROM adids_in_test_not_in_verification
    LIMIT 10
) t

with cjs as (
SELECT 
    dcr.job_hash,
    sum(cast(dcr.numhiresMade as int)) as numhiresMade,
    sum(cast(dcr.numHiresMadeIndeed as int)) as numHiresMadeIndeed,
    sum(cast(dcr.numHiresMadeExternal as int)) as numHiresMadeExternal
FROM datalake.imhotep.dradisClosedJobReason as dcr
WHERE dcr.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2024-04-01') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2024-10-24')
	and dcr.numhiresMade> '0'
group by 1
)
,job_id_job_hash_mapping as (
SELECT 
	jobhash_underscore, max(agg_job_id) as agg_job_id
FROM datalake.imhotep.job_id_job_hash_mapping
WHERE unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2024-10-23') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2024-10-24')
	and jobhash_underscore in (select distinct job_hash from cjs)
group by 1 
)
,jam as (
select 
	agg_job_id,
    max(job_product) as job_product,
    max(job_country_code) as job_country_code,
    sum(clicks) as clicks,
    sum(apply_starts) as apply_starts,
    sum(applies) as applies
from datalake.imhotep.jobactivitymetrics
where day between '2022-04-01' and 'today'	
	and agg_job_id in (select distinct agg_job_id from job_id_job_hash_mapping)
group by 1 
)

,view as (
select 
	job_id_job_hash_mapping.agg_job_id,
    coalesce(applies,0) as applies,
    coalesce(apply_starts,0) as apply_starts,
    coalesce(clicks,0) as clicks,
    numhiresMade,
    numHiresMadeIndeed,
    numHiresMadeExternal,
    job_product,
    job_country_code
from cjs 
join job_id_job_hash_mapping on job_id_job_hash_mapping.jobhash_underscore = cjs.job_hash
left join jam
	on job_id_job_hash_mapping.agg_job_id = jam.agg_job_id
)

    This does not flag instances that are not picking up the newest image on rebuild but that image is still less than 120 days old. Technically still patched, but on track to not be patched. 
    */
    , CASE WHEN 
        day(current_timestamp - from_iso8601_timestamp(e.launched_on)) <= 90 -- Must update at least every 90 days
        	AND day(current_timestamp - from_iso8601_timestamp(g.created_on)) <= 120 -- If the image it built from is over 120 days old, it's not following the golden image releases
        THEN 1
        ELSE 0
      END AS patched
    , 1 AS count
from ec2 e
INNER JOIN golden_amis g
ON e.image_id=g.id

  WHERE lib.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('60d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('1d')
  AND tm.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('60d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('1d')
),

app_base AS (
  SELECT
      tier_0,
      tier_1,
      tier_2,
      tier_3,
      tier_4,
      tier_5,
      tier_6,
      tier_7,
      tier_8,
      app.teamId,
      'app' AS resource_type,
      env,
      applicationRuntime AS languageRuntime,
      applicationName AS resource_name,
      lockdownAge AS age,
      app.day
  FROM applicationFreshnessSnapshot AS app
  LEFT JOIN teamwrksSnapshot tm
  ON app.teamid = tm.teamid
  AND app.day = DATE_FORMAT(CAST(tm.day AS TIMESTAMP), '%Y-%m-%d')
  WHERE app.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('60d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('1d')
  AND tm.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('60d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('1d')
)

  SELECT *

)

WITH

w_va as (
	SELECT source_id, advertiser_id
    FROM datalake.tiller.adsystemdb_tbladvertiserjobsource
    WHERE status = 'VERIFIED'
    GROUP BY 1,2),

w_sj as (
	SELECT date_format(DATE_TRUNC('WEEK', FROM_UNIXTIME(sj.unixtime)),'%Y-%m-%d') as weekStart
	, w_va.advertiser_id
    FROM datalake.imhotep.searchablejobs sj
	INNER JOIN w_va ON sj.sourceid = w_va.source_id
    WHERE unixtime between imhotep_unixtime(CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '183' DAY) 
	AND imhotep_unixtime(CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '1' DAY)
	AND jobcountry != 'JP'
	GROUP BY 1,2),
    
w_s as (
	SELECT date_format(DATE_TRUNC('WEEK', FROM_UNIXTIME(unixtime)),'%Y-%m-%d') as weekStart
	, CAST(advertiserid as BIGINT) as advertiser_id
    , COUNT(DISTINCT(requestTk)) as searches
    , COUNT(DISTINCT(CASE WHEN totalhitcount>0 
    	THEN requestTk ELSE NULL END)) as searchesWithResults
    , COUNT(DISTINCT(CASE WHEN totalhitcount>0 AND clickdepth_csv IS NOT NULL 
    	THEN requestTk ELSE NULL END)) as searchesWithResultsAndClick
	FROM datalake.imhotep.employerjobsearch
    WHERE unixtime between imhotep_unixtime(CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '183' DAY) 
		AND imhotep_unixtime(CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '1' DAY)
	AND lower(gqlOperationName) not like '%facet%' 
    AND lower(gqlOperationName) not like '%count%' 
    AND onehostmodule = './SimpleJobPicker' 
    /* ^^ Only inlcudes SJP until logging fix (EJSEARCH-1895) completes */
	AND country != 'JP'
    AND coalesce(is_privileged,0) != 1
    GROUP BY 1,2)
       
SELECT weekStart
, searches
, (searches-searchesWithResults) as searchesWithZeroResults
, searchesWithResultsAndClick
, format('%.2f%%', (cast(searchesWithResultsAndClick as double)/cast(searches as double)*100)) as netClickRate
FROM
    (SELECT w_s.weekStart
    , SUM(w_s.searches) as searches
    , SUM(w_s.searchesWithResults) as searchesWithResults
    , SUM(w_s.searchesWithResultsAndClick) as searchesWithResultsAndClick
    FROM w_s 
    INNER JOIN w_sj
        ON w_s.advertiser_id = w_sj.advertiser_id 
        AND w_s.weekstart = w_sj.weekstart
    GROUP BY 1)

WITH snapshot AS (
    SELECT 
	    acctid,
        resume.resumetype as resumetype,
        date_trunc('hour', from_unixtime(resume.datecreated)) AS hour_created
    FROM datalake.jssdi.profile_snapshot
    CROSS JOIN UNNEST(slice(array_sort(resumes, (r1, r2) -> IF(r1.datecreated<r2.datecreated, 1, IF(r1.datecreated=r2.datecreated, 0, -1))), 1, cardinality(resumes)-1)) AS resume -- get all resumes except first created
    WHERE 
	        day = '2024-10-24'
        AND CARDINALITY(resumes) > 1
), create_events AS (
	SELECT accountid, client, DATE_TRUNC('hour', FROM_UNIXTIME(unixtime)) AS hour_created
    FROM datalake.imhotep.profileevents
    WHERE unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2024-10-10') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2024-10-17')
    	AND (eventtype = 'RESUME_CREATED' OR eventtype = 'PROFILE_CREATED')
)
SELECT t1.hour_created, resumetype, t2.client, count(*) as count
FROM snapshot t1
LEFT JOIN create_events t2
	ON t1.acctid = t2.accountid AND t1.hour_created = t2.hour_created
WHERE t1.hour_created BETWEEN DATE_PARSE('2024-10-10', '%Y-%m-%d') AND DATE_PARSE('2024-10-17', '%Y-%m-%d')
GROUP BY t1.hour_created, resumetype, t2.client

WITH experiment_data AS (
	SELECT 
    	CASE WHEN ARRAYS_OVERLAP(ndxgrp, 
            ARRAY['#b15:idxmatchingcontrolplane_e275','#B15:idxmatchingcontrolplane_e275']) 
            THEN 'test' ELSE 'control' END AS _group, 
        q, jobid
    FROM sponsored -- TABLESAMPLE BERNOULLI (10) -- sampling rate
    WHERE 
    	unixtime >= imhotep_unixtime('2024-10-15') AND unixtime < imhotep_unixtime('2024-11-12') -- test start date & end date
        AND country = 'ca'
        AND ARRAYS_OVERLAP(ndxgrp, 
        	ARRAY['#b15:idxmatchingcontrolplane_e274','#B15:idxmatchingcontrolplane_e274',
            	  '#b15:idxmatchingcontrolplane_e275','#B15:idxmatchingcontrolplane_e275'])
)

SELECT 
	_group, 
    COUNT_IF(answer='No') as bad_matches, 
    COUNT() AS all_labels, 
    COUNT_IF(answer='No') / CAST(COUNT() AS DOUBLE) AS BMR
FROM jobtoqueryrelevance
INNER JOIN experiment_data ON
	jobtoqueryrelevance.query = experiment_data.q
    AND jobtoqueryrelevance.jobid = experiment_data.jobid
WHERE 
	jobtoqueryrelevance.unixtime >= imhotep_unixtime('2024-01-01') AND jobtoqueryrelevance.unixtime < imhotep_unixtime('2024-11-12')
	AND jobtoqueryrelevance.country='CA'
GROUP BY _group

WITH sub1 as (
    SELECT
    	DATE_FORMAT(FROM_UNIXTIME(ji.unixtime), '%Y-%m-%d') as date,
        tw.tier_0 AS t0,
        tw.tier_1 AS t1,
        COUNT(CASE WHEN
        	ji.status IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release') AND 
            (
              (
                  ji.priority = 'Blocker' AND
                  -- ji.resolutiontimestamp > 0 AND
                  -- last 30 days
                  (ji.unixtime - (TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000)) / 86400 <= 30 AND
                  -- SLO days to complete
                  (TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) - TRY_CAST(ji.createtimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 86400000 <= 30
              ) OR (
              	  -- Fallback to capture Critical and all other issues until bot updates to prevent data gaps 
                  ji.priority NOT IN ('Blocker') AND
                  -- ji.resolutiontimestamp > 0 AND
                  -- last 30 days
                  (ji.unixtime - (TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000)) / 86400 <= 30 AND
                  -- SLO days to complete
                  (TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) - TRY_CAST(ji.createtimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 86400000 <= 90
              )
            ) THEN 1 END
        ) AS REM_30,
        COUNT(
        	CASE WHEN
            	ji.status IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release') AND
            	-- ji.resolutiontimestamp > 0 AND
                (ji.unixtime - (TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000)) / 86400 <= 30
                THEN 1 END
        ) AS ALL_REM_30,
        COUNT(
        	CASE WHEN
            	(
                    ji.status NOT IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release')
            	    -- OR ji.resolutiontimestamp = 0
                ) AND (
                	(
                    	ji.priority = 'Blocker' AND
                        -- SLO days to complete
                		(ji.unixtime - (TRY_CAST(ji.createtimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000)) / 86400 > 30
                    ) OR (
                    	-- SLO days to complete
                    	ji.priority NOT IN ('Blocker') AND
                		(ji.unixtime - (TRY_CAST(ji.createtimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000)) / 86400 > 90
                    )
                )
                THEN 1 END
        ) AS UNREM
    FROM datalake.imhotep.jiracloudissues AS ji
    JOIN datalake.imhotep.ownershipSnapshot AS ow ON ji.projectkey = ow.key AND ji.day = ow.day

        WHERE day >= CAST(DATE_FORMAT(CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '7' DAY, '%Y-%m-%d') AS VARCHAR)

        WHERE day >= CAST(DATE_FORMAT(CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '7' DAY, '%Y-%m-%d') AS VARCHAR)

    END AS SLO_Score,

    UNREM AS Open_Outside_SLO,
    t1,

FROM (

        tw.tier_2 AS t2,
        tw.tier_3 AS t3,
        tw.tier_4 AS t4,
        tw.tier_5 AS t5,
        tw.tier_6 AS t6,
        tw.tier_7 AS t7,
        
        COUNT(CASE WHEN
        	ji.status IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release') AND 
            (
              (
                  ji.priority = 'Blocker' AND
                  -- last 30 days
                  ((ji.unixtime - TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 1000) / 86400 <= 30 AND
                  -- SLO days to complete

              ) OR (

                  ji.priority NOT IN ('Blocker') AND
                  -- last 30 days

              )
            ) THEN 1 END
        ) AS REM_30,
        COUNT(
        	CASE WHEN
            	ji.status IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release') AND
                -- last 30 days
                (ji.unixtime - TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 86400 <= 30
                THEN 1 END
        ) AS ALL_REM_30,
        COUNT(
        	CASE WHEN
            	(
                    ji.status NOT IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release')
                ) AND (
                	(
                    	ji.priority = 'Blocker' AND
                        -- SLO days to complete
                		(ji.unixtime - TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 86400 > 30
                    ) OR (
                    	-- SLO days to complete
                    	ji.priority NOT IN ('Blocker') AND
                		(ji.unixtime - TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 86400 > 90
                    )
                )
                THEN 1 END
        ) AS UNREM
    FROM datalake.imhotep.jiracloudissues AS ji
    JOIN datalake.imhotep.ownershipSnapshot AS ow ON ji.projectkey = ow.key
    JOIN datalake.imhotep.teamwrksSnapshot AS tw ON ow.accountablePartyId = tw.teamId
    WHERE

        ow.day = (SELECT most_recent_day from populated_day) AND
        tw.day = (SELECT most_recent_day from populated_day) AND
        ji.day >= CAST(DATE_FORMAT(CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '7' DAY, '%Y-%m-%d') AS VARCHAR) AND
        ow.day >= CAST(DATE_FORMAT(CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '7' DAY, '%Y-%m-%d') AS VARCHAR) AND
        tw.day >= CAST(DATE_FORMAT(CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '7' DAY, '%Y-%m-%d') AS VARCHAR) AND

    GROUP BY ow.accountablePartyId, ji.projectkey, tw.tier_1, tw.tier_2, tw.tier_3, tw.tier_4, tw.tier_5, tw.tier_6, tw.tier_7

            (ji.unixtime - TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 86400 <= 30

    ) IS NOT NULL AND (
        COUNT(
            CASE WHEN
                ji.status IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release') AND
                -- last 30 days
                (ji.unixtime - TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 86400 <= 30
                THEN 1 END
        ) + COUNT(
            CASE WHEN
                (
                    ji.status NOT IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release')
                ) AND (

                        (ji.unixtime - TRY_CAST(ji.createtimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000) / 86400 > 90

WITH sub1 as (
    SELECT
    	DATE_FORMAT(FROM_UNIXTIME(ji.unixtime), '%Y-%m-%d') as date,
        tw.tier_0 AS t0,
        tw.tier_1 AS t1,
        tw.tier_2 AS t2,
        tw.tier_3 AS t3,
        tw.tier_4 as t4,
        tw.tier_5 AS t5,
        COUNT(CASE WHEN
        	ji.status IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release') AND 
            (
              (
                  ji.priority = 'Blocker' AND
                  -- ji.resolutiontimestamp > 0 AND
                  -- last 30 days
                  (ji.unixtime - (TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000)) / 86400 <= 30 AND
                  -- SLO days to complete
                  (TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) - TRY_CAST(ji.createtimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 86400000 <= 30
              ) OR (
              	  -- Fallback to capture Critical and all other issues until bot updates to prevent data gaps 
                  ji.priority NOT IN ('Blocker') AND
                  -- ji.resolutiontimestamp > 0 AND
                  -- last 30 days
                  (ji.unixtime - (TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000)) / 86400 <= 30 AND
                  -- SLO days to complete
                  (TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) - TRY_CAST(ji.createtimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 86400000 <= 90
              )
            ) THEN 1 END
        ) AS REM_30,
        COUNT(
        	CASE WHEN
            	ji.status IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release') AND
            	-- ji.resolutiontimestamp > 0 AND
                (ji.unixtime - (TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000)) / 86400 <= 30
                THEN 1 END
        ) AS ALL_REM_30,
        COUNT(
        	CASE WHEN
            	(
                    ji.status NOT IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release')
            	    -- OR ji.resolutiontimestamp = 0
                ) AND (
                	(
                    	ji.priority = 'Blocker' AND
                        -- SLO days to complete
                		(ji.unixtime - (TRY_CAST(ji.createtimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000)) / 86400 > 30
                    ) OR (
                    	-- SLO days to complete
                    	ji.priority NOT IN ('Blocker') AND
                		(ji.unixtime - (TRY_CAST(ji.createtimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000)) / 86400 > 90
                    )
                )
                THEN 1 END
        ) AS UNREM
    FROM datalake.imhotep.jiracloudissues AS ji
    JOIN datalake.imhotep.ownershipSnapshot AS ow ON ji.projectkey = ow.key AND ji.day = ow.day
    JOIN datalake.imhotep.teamwrksSnapshot AS tw ON ow.accountablePartyId = tw.teamId AND tw.day = ow.day
    WHERE
        ji.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('30d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today') AND
        ow.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('30d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today') AND
        tw.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('30d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today') AND
        CONTAINS(TRANSFORM(ji.labelstok, s -> LOWER(s)), 'a11y') AND
        NOT CONTAINS(TRANSFORM(ji.labelstok, s -> LOWER(s)), 'a11y-exemption') AND
        -- ((ji.unixtime - (TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000)) / 86400 <= 30 OR ji.resolutiontimestamp = 0) AND
        ji.projectkey NOT IN  ('QL', 'A11Y', 'PIED', 'HIGHLANDER', 'JSA11Y', 'EMPA11Y', 'FIM', 'DSYNC', 'CHUBSERV', 'CHUBUI', 'COMMSHUB', 'CHUBSEND') AND
        ji.issuetype = 'Bug' AND
        LOWER(tw.tier_1) NOT IN ('global revenue', 'marketing') AND
		tw.tier_5 != 'Unspecified'
    GROUP BY DATE_FORMAT(FROM_UNIXTIME(ji.unixtime), '%Y-%m-%d'), tw.tier_0, tw.tier_1, tw.tier_2, tw.tier_3, tw.tier_4, tw.tier_5
)

SELECT
	date,
    t0,
    t1,
    t2,
    t3,
    t4,
    t5,
    CASE
    	WHEN ALL_REM_30 IS NULL OR (ALL_REM_30 + UNREM = 0) THEN 100
        ELSE ROUND((CAST(REM_30 AS DECIMAL(10, 2)) / (CAST(ALL_REM_30 AS DECIMAL(10, 2)) + CAST(UNREM AS DECIMAL(10, 2)))) * 100, 2)
    END AS SLO_Score,
    REM_30 AS Within_SLO,
    ALL_REM_30 AS Remediated_Last_30,
    UNREM AS Open_Outside_SLO
FROM sub1
WHERE
	(t0 = 'Indeed') AND
    ('Marketplace'='' OR t1 = 'Marketplace') AND
    (''='' OR t2 = '') AND
    (''='' OR t3 = '') AND
    (''='' OR t4 = '') AND

-- Secondary metric:  number of unique jobs identified as present in a repost cluster (including both copy and original in the cluster)

with
truth_copies as
(   select concat(radArtifactName, '-', modelId, '-', runStartTime) as model,
           date_trunc('day', from_unixtime(jobCopyCreateDate/1000)) as day,
           jobCopyJobId,
           count(*) as c
    from datalake.imhotep.duplicationDetectionRadContents
    where imhotep_unixtime('1d') <= unixtime and unixtime < imhotep_unixtime('1d') + 24*60*60
    and   modelId='Legacy RepostDetector'
    and   imhotep_unixtime('1000d') <= jobCopyCreateDate/1000 and jobCopyCreateDate/1000 < imhotep_unixtime('0d')
    group by 1,2,3 ),
truth_originals as
(   select concat(radArtifactName, '-', modelId, '-', runStartTime) as model,
           date_trunc('day', from_unixtime(jobCopyCreateDate/1000)) as day,
           originalJobId,
           count(*) as c
    from datalake.imhotep.duplicationDetectionRadContents
    where imhotep_unixtime('1d') <= unixtime and unixtime < imhotep_unixtime('1d') + 24*60*60
    and   modelId='Legacy RepostDetector'
    and   imhotep_unixtime('1000d') <= jobCopyCreateDate/1000 and jobCopyCreateDate/1000 < imhotep_unixtime('0d')
    group by 1,2,3 ),
truth_jobs as
(   select model, day, jobCopyJobId as jobId from truth_copies
    union
    select model, day, originalJobId as jobId from truth_originals ),
model_copies as
(   select concat(radArtifactName, '-', modelId, '-', runStartTime) as model,
           date_trunc('day', from_unixtime(jobCopyCreateDate/1000)) as day,
           jobCopyJobId as jobId,
           count(*) as c
    from datalake.imhotep.duplicationDetectionRadContents
    where imhotep_unixtime('1d') <= unixtime and unixtime < imhotep_unixtime('1d') + 24*60*60
    and   modelId='legacyRepostModel-2.2'
    and   imhotep_unixtime('1000d') <= jobCopyCreateDate/1000 and jobCopyCreateDate/1000 < imhotep_unixtime('0d')
    group by 1,2,3 ),
model_originals as
(   select concat(radArtifactName, '-', modelId, '-', runStartTime) as model,
           date_trunc('day', from_unixtime(jobCopyCreateDate/1000)) as day,
           originalJobId as jobId,
           count(*) as c
    from datalake.imhotep.duplicationDetectionRadContents
    where imhotep_unixtime('1d') <= unixtime and unixtime < imhotep_unixtime('1d') + 24*60*60
    and   modelId='legacyRepostModel-2.2'
    and   imhotep_unixtime('1000d') <= jobCopyCreateDate/1000 and jobCopyCreateDate/1000 < imhotep_unixtime('0d')
    group by 1,2,3 ),
model_jobs as
(   select model, day, jobId from model_copies
    union
    select model, day, jobId from model_originals ),
matches as
(   select coalesce(mj.day, tj.day) as day,
           tj.jobId is not null as truth_match,
           mj.jobId is not null as model_match
	from truth_jobs tj
    full outer join model_jobs mj on (    mj.model != tj.model
                                      and mj.day = tj.day
                                      and mj.jobId = tj.jobId)
),
venn as
(   select day,
           truth_match,
           model_match,
           count(*) as count
    from matches
    group by 1,2,3 ),
intersection_count as
(   select day,
           count
    from venn
    where truth_match
    and   model_match
),
union_count as
(   select day,
           sum(count) as count
    from venn -- ignoring truth_match and model_match fields
    group by 1 )
select ic.day,
       ic.count as intersection_count,
       uc.count as union_count,
       cast(ic.count as double) / cast(uc.count as double) as jaccard
from intersection_count ic,
     union_count uc
where ic.day = uc.day

yesterday as

    from datalake.imhotep.duplicationDetectionRadContents

-- create dates assigned in the artifact never change

with
today as
(   select concat(radArtifactName, '-', modelId, '-', runStartTime) as model,
           concat(radArtifactName, '-', modelId) as artifactModel,
           jobCopyJobId,
           jobCopyCreateDate,
           originalJobId,
           originalJobCreateDate
    from datalake.imhotep.duplicationDetectionRadContents
    where imhotep_unixtime('1d') <= unixtime and unixtime < imhotep_unixtime('1d') + 24*60*60
    and   imhotep_unixtime('1000d') <= jobCopyCreateDate/1000 and jobCopyCreateDate/1000 < imhotep_unixtime('0d')
),
yesterday as
(   select concat(radArtifactName, '-', modelId, '-', runStartTime) as model,
           concat(radArtifactName, '-', modelId) as artifactModel,
           jobCopyJobId,
           jobCopyCreateDate,
           originalJobId,
           originalJobCreateDate
    from datalake.imhotep.duplicationDetectionRadContents
    where imhotep_unixtime('1d') - 24*60*60 <= unixtime and unixtime < imhotep_unixtime('1d')
    and   imhotep_unixtime('1000d') <= jobCopyCreateDate/1000 and jobCopyCreateDate/1000 < imhotep_unixtime('0d')
)
select y.model as yesterday,
       t.model as today,
       y.jobCopyJobId,
       y.jobCopyCreateDate as yesterdayCopyCreate,
       t.jobCopyCreateDate as todayCopyCreate,
       y.originalJobId,
       y.originalJobCreateDate as yesterdayOriginalCreate,
       t.originalJobCreateDate as todayOriginalCreate
from yesterday y
join today t on (    t.artifactModel = y.artifactModel
                 and t.jobCopyJobId = y.jobCopyJobId
                 and t.originalJobId = y.originalJobId
                 and (   t.jobCopyCreateDate != y.jobCopyCreateDate
                      or t.originalJobCreateDate != y.originalJobCreateDate
                     )
                )

-- Primary metric:  jaccard similarity of MVP and legacy mappings (mappings of copy --> original)

with
distinct_non_truth_models as
(   select concat(radArtifactName, '-', modelId, '-', runStartTime) as compare_model, -- distinct models we want to compare against truth
           count(*)
    from datalake.imhotep.duplicationDetectionRadContents
    where imhotep_unixtime('1d') <= unixtime and unixtime < imhotep_unixtime('1d') + 24*60*60
    and   modelId='legacyRepostModel-2.2'
    and   imhotep_unixtime('1000d') <= jobCopyCreateDate/1000 and jobCopyCreateDate/1000 < imhotep_unixtime('0d')
    group by 1 ),
truth_mappings as
(   select concat(ddrc.radArtifactName, '-', ddrc.modelId, '-', runStartTime) as truth_model,
           dnlm.compare_model,
           date_trunc('day', from_unixtime(ddrc.jobCopyCreateDate/1000)) as day,
           ddrc.jobCopyJobId,
           ddrc.originalJobId
    from datalake.imhotep.duplicationDetectionRadContents ddrc,
         distinct_non_truth_models dnlm -- cross join to make a separate copy of each legacy record dedicated to comparing with a model
    where imhotep_unixtime('1d') <= ddrc.unixtime and ddrc.unixtime < imhotep_unixtime('1d') + 24*60*60
    and   ddrc.modelId='Legacy RepostDetector'
    and   imhotep_unixtime('1000d') <= ddrc.jobCopyCreateDate/1000 and ddrc.jobCopyCreateDate/1000 < imhotep_unixtime('0d')
),
model_mappings as
(   select concat(radArtifactName, '-', modelId, '-', runStartTime) as model,
           date_trunc('day', from_unixtime(jobCopyCreateDate/1000)) as day,
           jobCopyJobId,
           originalJobId
    from datalake.imhotep.duplicationDetectionRadContents
    where imhotep_unixtime('1d') <= unixtime and unixtime < imhotep_unixtime('1d') + 24*60*60
    and   modelId='legacyRepostModel-2.2'
    and   imhotep_unixtime('1000d') <= jobCopyCreateDate/1000 and jobCopyCreateDate/1000 < imhotep_unixtime('0d')
),
matches as
(   select coalesce(lm.day, mm.day) as day,
           -- could use any field, just detecting null from outer join, using jobCopyJobId
           lm.jobCopyJobId is not null as truth_match,
           mm.jobCopyJobId is not null as model_match
    from truth_mappings lm
    full outer join model_mappings mm
        on (    lm.compare_model = mm.model
            and lm.day = mm.day
            and lm.jobCopyJobId = mm.jobCopyJobId
            and lm.originalJobId = mm.originalJobId ) ),
venn as
(   select day,
           truth_match,
           model_match,
           count(*) as count
    from matches
    group by 1,2,3 ),
intersection_count as
(   select day,
           count
    from venn
    where truth_match
    and   model_match
),
union_count as
(   select day,
           sum(count) as count
    from venn -- ignoring truth_match and model_match fields
    group by 1 )
select ic.day,
       ic.count as intersection_count,
       uc.count as union_count,
       cast(ic.count as double) / cast(uc.count as double) as jaccard
from intersection_count ic,
     union_count uc
where ic.day = uc.day

WITH sub1 as (
    SELECT
    	DATE_FORMAT(FROM_UNIXTIME(ji.unixtime), '%Y-%m-%d') as date,
        tw.tier_0 AS t0,
        tw.tier_1 AS t1,
        tw.tier_2 AS t2,
        tw.tier_3 AS t3,
        COUNT(CASE WHEN
        	ji.status IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release') AND 
            (
              (
                  ji.priority = 'Blocker' AND
                  -- ji.resolutiontimestamp > 0 AND
                  -- last 30 days
                  (ji.unixtime - (TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000)) / 86400 <= 30 AND
                  -- SLO days to complete
                  (TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) - TRY_CAST(ji.createtimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 86400000 <= 30
              ) OR (
              	  -- Fallback to capture Critical and all other issues until bot updates to prevent data gaps 
                  ji.priority NOT IN ('Blocker') AND
                  -- ji.resolutiontimestamp > 0 AND
                  -- last 30 days
                  (ji.unixtime - (TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000)) / 86400 <= 30 AND
                  -- SLO days to complete
                  (TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) - TRY_CAST(ji.createtimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 86400000 <= 90
              )
            ) THEN 1 END
        ) AS REM_30,
        COUNT(
        	CASE WHEN
            	ji.status IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release') AND
            	-- ji.resolutiontimestamp > 0 AND
                (ji.unixtime - (TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000)) / 86400 <= 30
                THEN 1 END
        ) AS ALL_REM_30,
        COUNT(
        	CASE WHEN
            	(
                    ji.status NOT IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release')
            	    -- OR ji.resolutiontimestamp = 0
                ) AND (
                	(
                    	ji.priority = 'Blocker' AND
                        -- SLO days to complete
                		(ji.unixtime - (TRY_CAST(ji.createtimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000)) / 86400 > 30
                    ) OR (
                    	-- SLO days to complete
                    	ji.priority NOT IN ('Blocker') AND
                		(ji.unixtime - (TRY_CAST(ji.createtimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000)) / 86400 > 90
                    )
                )
                THEN 1 END
        ) AS UNREM
    FROM datalake.imhotep.jiracloudissues AS ji
    JOIN datalake.imhotep.ownershipSnapshot AS ow ON ji.projectkey = ow.key AND ji.day = ow.day
    JOIN datalake.imhotep.teamwrksSnapshot AS tw ON ow.accountablePartyId = tw.teamId AND tw.day = ow.day
    WHERE
        ji.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('30d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today') AND
        ow.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('30d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today') AND
        tw.unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('30d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today') AND
        CONTAINS(TRANSFORM(ji.labelstok, s -> LOWER(s)), 'a11y') AND
        NOT CONTAINS(TRANSFORM(ji.labelstok, s -> LOWER(s)), 'a11y-exemption') AND
        -- ((ji.unixtime - (TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000)) / 86400 <= 30 OR ji.resolutiontimestamp = 0) AND
        ji.projectkey NOT IN  ('QL', 'A11Y', 'PIED', 'HIGHLANDER', 'JSA11Y', 'EMPA11Y', 'FIM', 'DSYNC', 'CHUBSERV', 'CHUBUI', 'COMMSHUB', 'CHUBSEND') AND
        ji.issuetype = 'Bug' AND
        LOWER(tw.tier_1) NOT IN ('global revenue', 'marketing') AND
		tw.tier_3 != 'Unspecified'
    GROUP BY DATE_FORMAT(FROM_UNIXTIME(ji.unixtime), '%Y-%m-%d'), tw.tier_0, tw.tier_1, tw.tier_2, tw.tier_3
)

SELECT
	date,
    t0,
    t1,
    t2,
    t3,
    CASE
    	WHEN ALL_REM_30 IS NULL OR (ALL_REM_30 + UNREM = 0) THEN 100
        ELSE ROUND((CAST(REM_30 AS DECIMAL(10, 2)) / (CAST(ALL_REM_30 AS DECIMAL(10, 2)) + CAST(UNREM AS DECIMAL(10, 2)))) * 100, 2)
    END AS SLO_Score,
    REM_30 AS Within_SLO,
    ALL_REM_30 AS Remediated_Last_30,
    UNREM AS Open_Outside_SLO
FROM sub1
WHERE
	(t0 = 'Indeed') AND
    (''='' OR t1 = '') AND
    (''='' OR t2 = '') AND
    (''='' OR t3 = '')
ORDER BY date, t0, t1, t2, t3 ASC

-- Count of a11y violations remediated within SLO in the last 30 days / (All a11y violations remediated within last 30 days + Open issues outside SLO)
SELECT
    teamId,
	project,
    CASE
    	WHEN ALL_REM_30 IS NULL OR (ALL_REM_30 + UNREM = 0) THEN 100
        ELSE ROUND((CAST(REM_30 AS DECIMAL(10, 2)) / (CAST(ALL_REM_30 AS DECIMAL(10, 2)) + CAST(UNREM AS DECIMAL(10, 2)))) * 100, 2)
    END AS SLO_Score,
    REM_30 AS Closed_Within_SLO,
    ALL_REM_30 AS All_Remediated_Last_30,
    UNREM AS Open_Outside_SLO,
    t1,
    t2,
    t3,
    t4,
    t5,
    t6,
    t7
FROM (
	SELECT
    	ji.projectkey AS project,
    	ow.accountablePartyId AS teamId,
        tw.tier_1 AS t1,
        tw.tier_2 AS t2,
        tw.tier_3 AS t3,
        tw.tier_4 AS t4,
        tw.tier_5 AS t5,
        tw.tier_6 AS t6,
        tw.tier_7 AS t7,
        
        COUNT(CASE WHEN
        	ji.status IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release') AND 
            (
              (
                  ji.priority = 'Blocker' AND
                  -- last 30 days
                  ((ji.unixtime - TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 1000) / 86400 <= 30 AND
                  -- SLO days to complete
                  ((TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) - TRY_CAST(ji.createtimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 1000) / 86400000 <= 30
              ) OR (
              	  -- Fallback to capture Critical and all other issues until bot updates to prevent data gaps 
                  ji.priority NOT IN ('Blocker') AND
                  -- last 30 days
                  (ji.unixtime - TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000) / 86400 <= 30 AND
                  -- SLO days to complete
                  (TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT) - TRY_CAST(ji.createtimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000) / 86400000 <= 90
              )
            ) THEN 1 END
        ) AS REM_30,
        COUNT(
        	CASE WHEN
            	ji.status IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release') AND
                -- last 30 days
                (ji.unixtime - TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 86400 <= 30
                THEN 1 END
        ) AS ALL_REM_30,
        COUNT(
        	CASE WHEN
            	(
                    ji.status NOT IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release')
                ) AND (
                	(
                    	ji.priority = 'Blocker' AND
                        -- SLO days to complete
                		(ji.unixtime - TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 86400 > 30
                    ) OR (
                    	-- SLO days to complete
                    	ji.priority NOT IN ('Blocker') AND
                		(ji.unixtime - TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 86400 > 90
                    )
                )
                THEN 1 END
        ) AS UNREM
    FROM datalake.imhotep.jiracloudissues AS ji
    JOIN datalake.imhotep.ownershipSnapshot AS ow ON ji.projectkey = ow.key
    JOIN datalake.imhotep.teamwrksSnapshot AS tw ON ow.accountablePartyId = tw.teamId
    WHERE
        ji.day = (SELECT most_recent_day from populated_day) AND
        ow.day = (SELECT most_recent_day from populated_day) AND
        tw.day = (SELECT most_recent_day from populated_day) AND
        ji.day >= CAST(DATE_FORMAT(CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '7' DAY, '%Y-%m-%d') AS VARCHAR) AND
        ow.day >= CAST(DATE_FORMAT(CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '7' DAY, '%Y-%m-%d') AS VARCHAR) AND
        tw.day >= CAST(DATE_FORMAT(CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '7' DAY, '%Y-%m-%d') AS VARCHAR) AND
        CONTAINS(TRANSFORM(ji.labelstok, s -> LOWER(s)), 'a11y') AND
        NOT CONTAINS(TRANSFORM(ji.labelstok, s -> LOWER(s)), 'a11y-exemption') AND
        ji.projectkey NOT IN  ('QL', 'A11Y', 'PIED', 'HIGHLANDER', 'JSA11Y', 'EMPA11Y', 'FIM', 'DSYNC', 'CHUBSERV', 'CHUBUI', 'COMMSHUB', 'CHUBSEND') AND
        ji.issuetype = 'Bug' AND
        tw.tier_1 NOT IN ('Global Revenue', 'Marketing')
    GROUP BY ow.accountablePartyId, ji.projectkey, tw.tier_1, tw.tier_2, tw.tier_3, tw.tier_4, tw.tier_5, tw.tier_6, tw.tier_7
        HAVING COUNT(
        CASE WHEN
            ji.status IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release') AND
            -- last 30 days
            (ji.unixtime - TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 86400 <= 30
            THEN 1 END
    ) IS NOT NULL AND (
        COUNT(
            CASE WHEN
                ji.status IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release') AND
                -- last 30 days
                (ji.unixtime - TRY_CAST(ji.resolutiontimestamp AS BIGINT)) / 86400 <= 30
                THEN 1 END
        ) + COUNT(
            CASE WHEN
                (
                    ji.status NOT IN ('Closed', 'Done', 'Pending Code Cleanup', 'Pending Closure', 'Pending Analysis', 'Test Paused', 'Test in Progress', 'Pending Prod Release')
                ) AND (
                    (
                        ji.priority = 'Blocker' AND
                        -- SLO days to complete
                        (ji.unixtime - TRY_CAST(ji.createtimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000) / 86400 > 30
                    ) OR (
                        -- SLO days to complete
                        ji.priority NOT IN ('Blocker') AND
                        (ji.unixtime - TRY_CAST(ji.createtimestamp AS BIGINT) / 1000) / 86400 > 90
                    )
                )
                THEN 1 END
        ) > 0
    )
)

with jobs as (SELECT coalesce(parent_company_id, job_source_id+1000000) as parent_company_id 
, coalesce(max(parent_company_name), max(job_source_name)) as parent_company_name   
, min(job_source_id) as job_source_id
, count(distinct agg_job_id) as jobs_l30days 
, sum(organic_apply_starts) as orgAS_l30days 

FROM datalake.imhotep.jobactivitymetrics j
WHERE unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('30d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today')
and job_country_code = 'US' and is_job_searchable > 0 
--and parent_company_id is not null 
and advertiser_type not in ('Test', 'Indeed')
group by 1)

, rev as (select parent_company_id 
, sum(net_revenue_cents)/100 as spend_lyear 
FROM datalake.imhotep.grdm j 
WHERE unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('1y') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today') 
group by 1) 

, together as (select jobs.* 
, coalesce(spend_lyear, 0) as spend_lyear 
, coalesce(last_any_products, cast('2000-01-01' as date)) as last_revenue_date  -- if no last revenue date, then say they last spend in 2000 
, date_diff('day', coalesce(last_any_products, cast('2000-01-01' as date)), CURRENT_DATE) as days_since_last_spend 
from jobs 
left join rev on rev.parent_company_id = jobs.parent_company_id 
left join datalake.core.product_analytics_fct_first_last_activity_dates_parent f 
	on f.parent_company_id = jobs.parent_company_id
--where jobs_l30days > 100    
)
, together_ordered as (select *, 
ntile(10) over (order by jobs_l30days desc) as jobs_ntile -- 1 is most jobs 
, ntile(10) over (order by spend_lyear asc) as spend_ntile -- 1 is lowest spend 
, ntile(10) over (order by days_since_last_spend desc) as days_since_last_spend_ntile -- 1 is never spender
from together )

, together_ordered_fixed as (select parent_company_id  
, job_source_id
, parent_company_name 
, orgAS_l30days 
, jobs_l30days
, days_since_last_spend
, spend_lyear
, jobs_ntile 
, case when spend_lyear <= 0 then 1 else spend_ntile end as spend_ntile 
, case when days_since_last_spend > 9000 then 1 else days_since_last_spend_ntile end as days_since_last_spend_ntile

from together_ordered )

, rfm as (select * 
, jobs_ntile + spend_ntile + days_since_last_spend_ntile as rfm_unweighted 
, 1*jobs_ntile + 100*spend_ntile + 10*days_since_last_spend_ntile as rfm_weighted -- the higher this number the bigger the penalty
from together_ordered_fixed
order by 1*jobs_ntile + 100*spend_ntile + 10*days_since_last_spend_ntile desc
)

, jobs_first_hour as (SELECT sourceid
, jobid  
, max(normtitle) as normtitle 
, coalesce(max(jlmsa), 'rural') as msa 
, sum(coalesce(applystarts,0)) as applystarts

FROM datalake.imhotep.mobileorganic j
WHERE unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('30d') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today')
and country in ('us', 'US') and jobageminutes <= 60
group by 1, 2)

, jobs_first_hour_ordered as (SELECT * 
, ntile(10) over (order by applystarts asc) as job_ntile
FROM jobs_first_hour)


, subset as (select case when rfm_weighted > 1000 then 'A_1000+ Biggest Penalty'
when rfm_weighted > 900 then 'B_900'
when rfm_weighted > 800 then 'C_800'
when rfm_weighted > 700 then 'D_700'
when rfm_weighted > 600 then 'E_600'
when rfm_weighted > 500 then 'F_500'
when rfm_weighted > 400 then 'G_400'
when rfm_weighted > 300 then 'H_300'
when rfm_weighted > 200 then 'I_200' else 'J_100 Lowest Penalty' end as rfm_segment 
, rfm.* 
, j.* 
, row_number() over (partition by job_source_id order by applystarts desc) as rn 

from rfm  
left join jobs_first_hour_ordered j on j.sourceid = rfm.job_source_id 
where rfm_weighted > 1000 or rfm_weighted < 200
and j.job_ntile = 10 )

select * from subset 
where rn <= 5 and orgAS_l30days > 10000

with app_status as(SELECT ats,apply_id, disposition_status, max(unixtime) as unixtime
FROM signal_back_disposition a
WHERE 
  -- remove apply_id that existed 1y before july
  NOT EXISTS (
      SELECT apply_id
      FROM signal_back_disposition b
      WHERE unixtime between imhotep_unixtime('2023-04-01') and imhotep_unixtime('2024-07-01')
        AND a.apply_id=b.apply_id
  )
  -- apply_id first appears in july
  AND EXISTS (
      SELECT apply_id
      FROM signal_back_disposition c
      WHERE unixtime between imhotep_unixtime('2024-07-01') and imhotep_unixtime('2024-08-01')
        AND a.apply_id=c.apply_id
  )
  AND unixtime between imhotep_unixtime('2024-07-01') and imhotep_unixtime('today')
  
  GROUP BY 1,2,3
)
,max_times as (
SELECT ats
, apply_id
, disposition_status
, unixtime
, ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY apply_id ORDER BY unixtime ASC) as status_number
, COUNT(*) OVER(PARTITION BY apply_id) as total_signals_for_apply
FROM app_status)

SELECT apply_id, total_signals_for_apply, status_number, FROM_UNIXTIME(unixtime) as disposition_date, disposition_status
FROM max_times
WHERE ats='ukg-prodd'
AND total_signals_for_apply=1 AND disposition_status='NEW'
ORDER BY 1,3

limit 500

WITH

w_va as (
	SELECT source_id, advertiser_id
    FROM datalake.tiller.adsystemdb_tbladvertiserjobsource
    WHERE status = 'VERIFIED'
    GROUP BY 1,2),

w_sj as (
	SELECT date_format(DATE_TRUNC('WEEK', FROM_UNIXTIME(sj.unixtime)),'%Y-%m-%d') as weekStart
	, w_va.advertiser_id
    FROM datalake.imhotep.searchablejobs sj
	INNER JOIN w_va ON sj.sourceid = w_va.source_id
    WHERE unixtime between imhotep_unixtime(CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '183' DAY) 
	AND imhotep_unixtime(CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '1' DAY)
	AND jobcountry != 'JP'
	GROUP BY 1,2),

w_oi as (
	SELECT date_format(DATE_TRUNC('WEEK', FROM_UNIXTIME(unixtime)),'%Y-%m-%d') as weekStart
    , advertiser_id 
    from datalake.imhotep.employer_user_actions_spark
    WHERE unixtime between imhotep_unixtime(CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '183' DAY) 
		AND imhotep_unixtime(CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '1' DAY)
    AND country != 'JP'
    AND is_privileged != 1
    GROUP BY 1,2),
    
w_s as (
	SELECT date_format(DATE_TRUNC('WEEK', FROM_UNIXTIME(unixtime)),'%Y-%m-%d') as weekStart
	, CAST(advertiserid as BIGINT) as advertiser_id
	FROM datalake.imhotep.employerjobsearch
    WHERE unixtime between imhotep_unixtime(CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '183' DAY) 
		AND imhotep_unixtime(CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '1' DAY)
	AND lower(gqlOperationName) not like '%facet%' 
    AND lower(gqlOperationName) not like '%count%' 
	AND country != 'JP'
    AND coalesce(is_privileged,0) != 1
    GROUP BY 1,2)
       
SELECT w_sj.weekStart
, count(DISTINCT(w_sj.advertiser_id)) as advIdsWithJob
, count(DISTINCT(w_oi.advertiser_id)) as advIdsOnIndeed
, count(DISTINCT(w_s.advertiser_id)) as advIdsWithSearch
FROM w_sj
LEFT JOIN w_oi 
	ON w_sj.advertiser_id = w_oi.advertiser_id
	AND w_sj.weekstart = w_oi.weekstart
LEFT JOIN w_s
	ON w_sj.advertiser_id = w_s.advertiser_id
	AND w_sj.weekstart = w_s.weekstart
GROUP BY 1

with status_change as (
select 
	cast(adv_id as int) as advertiser_id, cast(cand_id as int) as candidate_id, cand_new_status, unixtime
FROM datalake.imhotep.candStatusChange2
WHERE unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2017-01-01') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today')
union distinct 
select 
	advid as advertiser_id, candid as candidate_id, candnewstatus as cand_new_status, unixtime
from datalake.imhotep.dradiscandstatuschange
where unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2017-01-01') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today')
)
,hires as (
select from_unixtime(unixtime) as hire_timestamp, advertiser_id, candidate_id, cand_new_status 
from status_change 
where cand_new_status = 'Hired'
	and unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2019-01-01') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today')
)

,job_id_mapping AS (
SELECT a.advertiser_id
          ,a.candidate_id
          ,MAX(a.candidate_account_id) AS accountid
          ,MAX(a.agg_job_id) AS agg_job_id
          ,MAX(a.ats_job_id) AS ats_job_id
          ,MAX(a.indeed_apply_ctk) AS indeed_apply_ctk
          ,MAX(a.apply_id) AS apply_id
          ,MAX(a.date_created) AS indeed_apply_timestamp
    FROM datalake.imhotep.candidate_apply AS a
    INNER JOIN hires AS b
    ON a.advertiser_id = b.advertiser_id
    AND a.candidate_id = b.candidate_id
    where unixtime BETWEEN IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('2017-01-01') AND IMHOTEP_UNIXTIME('today')
    GROUP BY 1, 2
)

,view as (
select 
  csc.advertiser_id, 
  csc.candidate_id, 
  min(hire_timestamp) as hire_timestamp,
  min(job_id_mapping.indeed_apply_timestamp) as indeed_apply_timestamp, 
  min(case when csc.cand_new_status = 'Interviewed' then FROM_UNIXTIME(csc.unixtime) end) as interview_timestamp,
  min(case when csc.cand_new_status = 'Reviewed' then FROM_UNIXTIME(csc.unixtime) end) as reviewed_timestamp,
  min(case when csc.cand_new_status = 'Phone Screened' then FROM_UNIXTIME(csc.unixtime) end) as phone_screen_timestamp,
  MAX(accountid) AS accountid,
  MAX(agg_job_id) AS agg_job_id,
  MAX(ats_job_id) AS ats_job_id,
  MAX(indeed_apply_ctk) AS indeed_apply_ctk,
  MAX(apply_id) AS apply_id
from status_change as csc
join hires on hires.advertiser_id = cast(csc.advertiser_id as int) and hires.candidate_id = cast(csc.candidate_id as int) and csc.cand_new_status != 'Hired'
join job_id_mapping on job_id_mapping.advertiser_id = cast(csc.advertiser_id as int) and job_id_mapping.candidate_id = cast(csc.candidate_id as int)
group by 1,2
)
select 
	date_trunc('month', hire_timestamp)	as month,
    COUNT(*) AS hires,
    avg(date_diff('day', indeed_apply_timestamp, phone_screen_timestamp)) as time_to_contacting,
    sum(Case when phone_screen_timestamp is not null then 1 else 0 end) as hires_w_contacting,
    avg(date_diff('day', indeed_apply_timestamp, hire_timestamp)) as time_to_hire,
    avg(date_diff('day', indeed_apply_timestamp, reviewed_timestamp)) as time_to_review,
    avg(date_diff('day', reviewed_timestamp, hire_timestamp)) as time_review_to_hire
from view
group by 1
order by 1
